The paper deals with the design of location privacy preserving mechanisms (LPPMs) for location-based services (LBSs), which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a method for creating LPPMs that are customized for a user's mobility profile, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and data management (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the privacy and quality of service requirements of LPPMs, which is related to social and information sciences (cs.SI). Finally, the paper formulates the LPPM design problem as a Bayesian Stackelberg game, which is a topic related to control theory (cs.CY).
